                  </persName>
            . I am shopman to Mr. Braithwaite, a <rs id="t18280221-268-viclabel1423" type="occupation">brazier</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18280221-268-victim1517 t18280221-268-viclabel1423"></join>, of New-road, Surrey-square. The prisoner was eight or nine years in his employ - I went to his lodging, in Little Brook-street; I sent for an officer, who found these tools there - they are what we work with; the men never take the tools home, without leave - if he had asked leave he might have taken them; some men work at home, but the prisoner did not - he has only a small room.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18280221-268-person1519">
                  WILLIAM 
                  HEATH
